				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/steeltitan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1871133); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1871133&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164667" alt="Steeltitan" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1871133)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/steeltitan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1871133); return false;" >Steeltitan</a></span> <span class="odate time_1412465848 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Oct 2014 23:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2124655">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;way&nbsp;too&nbsp;much&nbsp;info</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;I'm&nbsp;so&nbsp;smart,&nbsp;right?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>[In the story, most of the groups aren't in Iran, and some aren't even in the middle east. They're just inside the ORIA's sphere of influence. In the tale, they mention people captured in Pakistan, Tunisia (which is in Africa,) Oman, Afghanistan, and East Jerusalem, which is a pretty big sphere of influence.</p>
<p>Someone will probably bring up the point how Iran can capture people in other nations. The things is, many of the above mentioned areas are also Islamic, and may take offense at foreign organizations taking bizarre and possibly dangerous artifacts out of their country. So while they do not openly support Iran, they may turn a blind eye to the capturing of foreign agents, especially if they are of religious nature. For example, Saudi Arabia bans christian missionaries from working in it. What would they think of a CotBG cultist? Besides which, the ORIA isn't stationing battalions of soldiers all the time. Most of the captures are probably by small teams, which are easier to tolerate.</p>
<p>Finally, Iran can probably get its teams in using anomalous artifacts. This can also explain how AWCY, Prometheus labs, Dr. Wondertainment's agents and the Serpent's Hand got in.</p>
<p>As for MC&amp;D, they can just Bribe their way in to any country]</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

