															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eskobar" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1173523); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1173523&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164667" alt="Eskobar" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1173523)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eskobar" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1173523); return false;" >Eskobar</a></span> <span class="odate time_1412472318 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Oct 2014 01:25</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2124689">
									

<p>Well, the way I figured it, most of the Groups of Interest <em>are</em> worth paying interest to <em>because</em> they have some kind of global or large-scale influence; otherwise, they'd just be <em>anomalous</em> and the Foundation could absorb/contain/suppress/amnesticize their membership, which would probably be their MO for all these groups if they could get away with it.</p>
<p>Now, I won't deny that all of the GoIs being involved in this particular year's roundup is the most plausible thing in the world, rather than a fun exercise in seeing how to make all the jigsaw pieces fall into place; and for that reason, I get that it's not everyone's bag. But given that this iteration of ORIA is active throughout the entire Muslim-majority world, there's a much bigger net to cover than just Tehran.</p>

							</div>

								
					
